      • create

        <T> java.util.Queue<T> create(int capacity)
        The queue must define at least 3 methods: poll(), offer() and isEmpty().

        The queue must be thread-safe. The easiest way to achieve this is by using lock (synchronized block etc).

        Do not use clever lock-free structures. They are not for you. For instance, most JCTools queues will not work with this library.

        Parameters:
        capacity - Bounded queue capacity, if 0 queue is unbounded.
